{'push_id': 9123894518, 'size': 16, 'distinct_size': 5, 'ref': 'refs/heads/jsonrpc', 'head': '8b80111b446658e657488656689fb72d92929441', 'before': '050f354d467d43105b7a7083e7654a8aff1b38cb', 'commits': [{'sha': '4e7d3ada289464551d2449ebfe2b4a8271677758', 'author': {'email': 'jmonk@dream-crushed.com', 'name': 'Jason Monk'}, 'message': 'Update kotlin to 1.6 and dependencies to newer

Bump the minor version to push a new version', 'distinct': False, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Monkopedia/ksrpc/commits/4e7d3ada289464551d2449ebfe2b4a8271677758'}, {'sha': 'f97bcdf658763fbf3c5d38f378d2b6be6b449553', 'author': {'email': 'jmonk@dream-crushed.com', 'name': 'Jason Monk'}, 'message': 'Merge in bidi work

This reworks a lot of the structure of communication here.

Channels are now split into 2 levels, SerializedChannel which is a whole
communication pathway, and SerializedService which can be split out into
multiple SerializedServices in parallel based on ChannelId.

On top of this is support for SerializedChannels to be either
a ChannelHost (can host services and sub-services), a ChannelClient (can
call into services or sub-services), or a Connection, which allows full
bidirectional communication acting as both a ChannelClient and
ChannelHost.

{'push_id': 9042418000, 'size': 1, 'distinct_size': 1, 'ref': 'refs/heads/main', 'head': 'f97bcdf658763fbf3c5d38f378d2b6be6b449553', 'before': '4e7d3ada289464551d2449ebfe2b4a8271677758', 'commits': [{'sha': 'f97bcdf658763fbf3c5d38f378d2b6be6b449553', 'author': {'email': 'jmonk@dream-crushed.com', 'name': 'Jason Monk'}, 'message': 'Merge in bidi work

This reworks a lot of the structure of communication here.

Channels are now split into 2 levels, SerializedChannel which is a whole
communication pathway, and SerializedService which can be split out into
multiple SerializedServices in parallel based on ChannelId.

On top of this is support for SerializedChannels to be either
a ChannelHost (can host services and sub-services), a ChannelClient (can
call into services or sub-services), or a Connection, which allows full
bidirectional communication acting as both a ChannelClient and
ChannelHost.
